content.description: Start in the same spot as Not All It's Cracked Up, instead of veering left to the crack, go straight up climbing the flake to the quartz sloper/jug. Continue straight, up crimps and a few jugs here and there. Fun face climbing. Anchors are far from the cliff face, so bring a long sling or a static line.
content.location: Middle of Warm-Up Wall, Blue in the beta photo. To the left of the roof with the ashes in it. (Same start as Not All It's Cracked Up to Be).

climbs.name: Not All It's Cracked Up to Be

content.description: Sorta fun dirty crack on the right side of the Warm-Up wall. Very easy climbing until the top where the hands get somewhat thin. The tree anchors are very solid, however they are set back quite a bit from the cliff so bring a long sling or a static line.
content.location: The start is located in the middle of the Warm-Up wall. This is the red climb in the beta photo.

content.description: Go up a decent flake to the right, then going straight/slightly right on a bunch nice pockets and crimps until the top out which ends in essentially the same as Quartz Shrimp. Fun variation of movement, with smaller feet and smaller crimps than Quartz. This is the yellow climb in the beta photo. Good anchors on the trees behind the cliff, however they are set back quite a bit from the face, so definitely bring a long sling or a decently long static line.
content.location: Start next to the roof with the ashes, going slightly right and up the slight bulge. This is the yellow climb in the beta photo.

content.description: Nice easy problem for warming up in snake den.
content.location: Follow the trail past Matchstick. It's the far end of the fourth crag.

content.description: Great warmup wall with many easy climbs.
